{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.38",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 38,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 38",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 38 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:1",
      "text": "And after Elius had ceased from speaking, the Lord spoke to Job through the whirlwind and clouds, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:2",
      "text": "Who is this that hides counsel from me, and confines words in his heart, and thinks to conceal them from me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:3",
      "text": "Gird thy loins like a man; and I will ask thee, and do thou answer me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:4",
      "text": "Where wast thou when I founded the earth? tell me now, if thou hast knowledge,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:5",
      "text": "who set the measures of it, if thou knowest? or who stretched a line upon it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:6",
      "text": "On what are its rings fastened? and who is he that laid the corner-stone upon it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:7",
      "text": "When the stars were made, all my angels praised me with a loud voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:8",
      "text": "And I shut up the sea with gates, when it rushed out, coming forth out of its mother's womb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:9",
      "text": "And I made a cloud its clothing, and swathed it in mist.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:10",
      "text": "And I set bounds to it, surrounding it with bars and gates.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:11",
      "text": "And I said to it, Hitherto shalt thou come, but thou shalt not go beyond, but thy waves shall be confined within thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:12",
      "text": "Or did I order the morning light in thy time; and did the morning star then first see his appointed place;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:13",
      "text": "to lay hold of the extremities of the earth, to cast out the ungodly out of it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:14",
      "text": "Or didst thou take clay of the ground, and form a living creature, and set it with the power of speech upon the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:15",
      "text": "And hast thou removed light from the ungodly, and crushed the arm of the proud?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:16",
      "text": "Or hast thou gone to the source of the sea, and walked in the tracks of the deep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:17",
      "text": "And do the gates of death open to thee for fear; and did the porters of hell quake when they saw thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:18",
      "text": "And hast thou been instructed in the breadth of the whole earth under heaven? tell me now, what is the extent of it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:19",
      "text": "And in what kind of a land does the light dwell? and of what kind is the place of darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:20",
      "text": "If thou couldest bring me to their utmost boundaries, and if also thou knowest their paths;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:21",
      "text": "I know then that thou wert born at that time, and the number of thy years is great.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:22",
      "text": "But hast thou gone to the treasures of snow? and hast thou seen the treasures of hail?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:23",
      "text": "And is there a store of them, for thee against the time of thine enemies, for the day of wars and battle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:24",
      "text": "And whence proceeds the frost? or whence is the south wind dispersed over the whole world under heaven?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:25",
      "text": "And who prepared a course for the violent rain, and a way for the thunders;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:26",
      "text": "to rain upon the land where there is no man, the wilderness, where there is not a man in it; so as to feed the untrodden and uninhabited land,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:27",
      "text": "and cause it to send forth a crop of green herbs?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:28",
      "text": "Who is the rain's father? and who has generated the drops of dew?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:29",
      "text": "And out of whose womb comes the ice? and who has produced the frost in the sky,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:30",
      "text": "which descends like flowing water? who has terrified the face of the ungodly?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:31",
      "text": "And dost thou understand the band of Pleias, and hast thou opened the barrier of Orion?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:32",
      "text": "Or wilt thou reveal Mazuroth in his season, and the evening star with his rays? Wilt thou guide them?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:33",
      "text": "And knowest thou the changes of heaven, or the events which take place together under heaven?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:34",
      "text": "And wilt thou call a cloud with thy voice, and will it obey thee with a violent shower of much rain?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:35",
      "text": "And wilt thou send lightnings, and they shall go? and shall they say to thee, What is thy pleasure?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:36",
      "text": "And who has given to women skill in weaving, or knowledge of embroidery?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.37",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:37",
      "text": "And who is he that numbers the clouds in wisdom, and has bowed the heaven down to the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.38",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:38",
      "text": "For it is spread out as dusty earth, and I have cemented it as one hewn stone to another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.39",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:39",
      "text": "And wilt thou hunt a prey for the lions? and satisfy the desires of the serpents?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.40",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:40",
      "text": "For they fear in their lairs, and lying in wait couch in the woods.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.38.41",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:41",
      "text": "And who has prepared food for the raven? for its young ones wander and cry to the Lord, in search of food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
